The paper deals with video classification using deep learning techniques, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also introduces novel methods for temporal encoding and feature extraction, which are relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper uses convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for feature extraction, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
